      "timestamp": "2026-06-22T17:45:56.691939+00:00",
      "type": "tool_result",
      "content": "```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"call_67614cc2e50a4dcd90b0ded8\",\n  \"name\": \"filesystem\",\n  \"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"range\\\": \\\"1880-2000\\\",\\n  \\\"lines\\\": {\\n    \\\"1880\\\": \\\"    def resizeEvent(self, event: QResizeEvent) -> None:  # type: ignore[override]\\\",\\n    \\\"1881\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Reapply column sizing and margins when the widget is resized.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1882\\\": \\\"        super().resizeEvent(event)\\\",\\n    \\\"1883\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1884\\\": \\\"        if self._tab_columns:\\\",\\n    \\\"1885\\\": \\\"            self.show_all_columns()\\\",\\n    \\\"1886\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1887\\\": \\\"        QTimer.singleShot(0, self._refresh_current_tab_thumbnails)\\\",\\n    \\\"1888\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1889\\\": \\\"        if self._tab_overview is not None and self._tab_overview.isVisible():\\\",\\n    \\\"1890\\\": \\\"            self.show_tab_overview()\\\",\\n    \\\"1891\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1892\\\": \\\"        elif self._tab_carousel is not None and self._tab_carousel.isVisible():\\\",\\n    \\\"1893\\\": \\\"            self.show_tab_carousel()\\\",\\n    \\\"1894\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1895\\\": \\\"    def show_all_columns(self) -> None:\\\",\\n    \\\"1896\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Show all columns, sizing each to its preferred width where possible.\\\",\\n    \\\"1897\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1898\\\": \\\"        Each column is sized to its preferred width. Tabs that return None from preferred_width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1899\\\": \\\"        are treated as having the zoom-scaled default preferred width. If the total of all column\\\",\\n    \\\"1900\\\": \\\"        widths is less than the available width, symmetric spacers centre the content.\\\",\\n    \\\"1901\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1902\\\": \\\"        if len(self._tab_columns) == 0:\\\",\\n    \\\"1903\\\": \\\"            return\\\",\\n    \\\"1904\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1905\\\": \\\"        min_col_width = 200\\\",\\n    \\\"1906\\\": \\\"        style_manager = self._style_manager\\\",\\n    \\\"1907\\\": \\\"        default_col_width = int(style_manager.nice_tab_width() * style_manager.zoom_factor())\\\",\\n    \\\"1908\\\": \\\"        available = self.width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1909\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1910\\\": \\\"        # Compute each column's preferred width. Tabs returning None use the default.\\\",\\n    \\\"1911\\\": \\\"        col_preferred: List[int] = []\\\",\\n    \\\"1912\\\": \\\"        for column in self._tab_columns:\\\",\\n    \\\"1913\\\": \\\"            pref: int | None = None\\\",\\n    \\\"1914\\\": \\\"            for i in range(column.count()):\\\",\\n    \\\"1915\\\": \\\"                tab = cast(TabBase, column.widget(i))\\\",\\n    \\\"1916\\\": \\\"                tab_pref = tab.preferred_width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1917\\\": \\\"                if tab_pref is not None:\\\",\\n    \\\"1918\\\": \\\"                    pref = tab_pref if pref is None else max(pref, tab_pref)\\\",\\n    \\\"1919\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1920\\\": \\\"            col_preferred.append(pref if pref is not None else default_col_width)\\\",\\n    \\\"1921\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1922\\\": \\\"        total_preferred = sum(max(min_col_width, p) for p in col_preferred)\\\",\\n    \\\"1923\\\": \\\"        sizes = [min_col_width] * len(self._tab_columns)\\\",\\n    \\\"1924\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1925\\\": \\\"        total_preferred += self._column_splitter.handleWidth() * (len(self._tab_columns) - 1)\\\",\\n    \\\"1926\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1927\\\": \\\"        if total_preferred <= available:\\\",\\n    \\\"1928\\\": \\\"            # Enough room: give each column its preferred width and centre with spacers.\\\",\\n    \\\"1929\\\": \\\"            for i, p in enumerate(col_preferred):\\\",\\n    \\\"1930\\\": \\\"                sizes[i] = max(min_col_width, p)\\\",\\n    \\\"1931\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1932\\\": \\\"            margin = (available - total_preferred) // 2\\\",\\n    \\\"1933\\\": \\\"            self._left_spacer.setFixedWidth(margin)\\\",\\n    \\\"1934\\\": \\\"            self._right_spacer.setFixedWidth(margin)\\\",\\n    \\\"1935\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1936\\\": \\\"        else:\\\",\\n    \\\"1937\\\": \\\"            # Not enough room: scale proportionally, no spacers.\\\",\\n    \\\"1938\\\": \\\"            scale = available / total_preferred\\\",\\n    \\\"1939\\\": \\\"            for i, p in enumerate(col_preferred):\\\",\\n    \\\"1940\\\": \\\"                sizes[i] = max(min_col_width, int(p * scale))\\\",\\n    \\\"1941\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1942\\\": \\\"            self._left_spacer.setFixedWidth(0)\\\",\\n    \\\"1943\\\": \\\"            self._right_spacer.setFixedWidth(0)\\\",\\n    \\\"1944\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1945\\\": \\\"        self._column_splitter.setSizes(sizes)\\\",\\n    \\\"1946\\\": \\\"        self._columns_layout.invalidate()\\\"\\n  }\\n}\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n`content` is:\n```json\n{\n  \"range\": \"1880-2000\",\n  \"lines\": {\n    \"1880\": \"    def resizeEvent(self, event: QResizeEvent) -> None:  # type: ignore[override]\",\n    \"1881\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Reapply column sizing and margins when the widget is resized.\\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"1882\": \"        super().resizeEvent(event)\",\n    \"1883\": \"\",\n    \"1884\": \"        if self._tab_columns:\",\n    \"1885\": \"            self.show_all_columns()\",\n    \"1886\": \"\",\n    \"1887\": \"        QTimer.singleShot(0, self._refresh_current_tab_thumbnails)\",\n    \"1888\": \"\",\n    \"1889\": \"        if self._tab_overview is not None and self._tab_overview.isVisible():\",\n    \"1890\": \"            self.show_tab_overview()\",\n    \"1891\": \"\",\n    \"1892\": \"        elif self._tab_carousel is not None and self._tab_carousel.isVisible():\",\n    \"1893\": \"            self.show_tab_carousel()\",\n    \"1894\": \"\",\n    \"1895\": \"    def show_all_columns(self) -> None:\",\n    \"1896\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Show all columns, sizing each to its preferred width where possible.\",\n    \"1897\": \"\",\n    \"1898\": \"        Each column is sized to its preferred width. Tabs that return None from preferred_width()\",\n    \"1899\": \"        are treated as having the zoom-scaled default preferred width. If the total of all column\",\n    \"1900\": \"        widths is less than the available width, symmetric spacers centre the content.\",\n    \"1901\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"1902\": \"        if len(self._tab_columns) == 0:\",\n    \"1903\": \"            return\",\n    \"1904\": \"\",\n    \"1905\": \"        min_col_width = 200\",\n    \"1906\": \"        style_manager = self._style_manager\",\n    \"1907\": \"        default_col_width = int(style_manager.nice_tab_width() * style_manager.zoom_factor())\",\n    \"1908\": \"        available = self.width()\",\n    \"1909\": \"\",\n    \"1910\": \"        # Compute each column's preferred width. Tabs returning None use the default.\",\n    \"1911\": \"        col_preferred: List[int] = []\",\n    \"1912\": \"        for column in self._tab_columns:\",\n    \"1913\": \"            pref: int | None = None\",\n    \"1914\": \"            for i in range(column.count()):\",\n    \"1915\": \"                tab = cast(TabBase, column.widget(i))\",\n    \"1916\": \"                tab_pref = tab.preferred_width()\",\n    \"1917\": \"                if tab_pref is not None:\",\n    \"1918\": \"                    pref = tab_pref if pref is None else max(pref, tab_pref)\",\n    \"1919\": \"\",\n    \"1920\": \"            col_preferred.append(pref if pref is not None else default_col_width)\",\n    \"1921\": \"\",\n    \"1922\": \"        total_preferred = sum(max(min_col_width, p) for p in col_preferred)\",\n    \"1923\": \"        sizes = [min_col_width] * len(self._tab_columns)\",\n    \"1924\": \"\",\n    \"1925\": \"        total_preferred += self._column_splitter.handleWidth() * (len(self._tab_columns) - 1)\",\n    \"1926\": \"\",\n    \"1927\": \"        if total_preferred <= available:\",\n    \"1928\": \"            # Enough room: give each column its preferred width and centre with spacers.\",\n    \"1929\": \"            for i, p in enumerate(col_preferred):\",\n    \"1930\": \"                sizes[i] = max(min_col_width, p)\",\n    \"1931\": \"\",\n    \"1932\": \"            margin = (available - total_preferred) // 2\",\n    \"1933\": \"            self._left_spacer.setFixedWidth(margin)\",\n    \"1934\": \"            self._right_spacer.setFixedWidth(margin)\",\n    \"1935\": \"\",\n    \"1936\": \"        else:\",\n    \"1937\": \"            # Not enough room: scale proportionally, no spacers.\",\n    \"1938\": \"            scale = available / total_preferred\",\n    \"1939\": \"            for i, p in enumerate(col_preferred):\",\n    \"1940\": \"                sizes[i] = max(min_col_width, int(p * scale))\",\n    \"1941\": \"\",\n    \"1942\": \"            self._left_spacer.setFixedWidth(0)\",\n    \"1943\": \"            self._right_spacer.setFixedWidth(0)\",\n    \"1944\": \"\",\n    \"1945\": \"        self._column_splitter.setSizes(sizes)\",\n    \"1946\": \"        self._columns_layout.invalidate()\"\n  }\n}\n```",
