      "content": "```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"call_4dc7bf633a444cbbbd91192f\",\n  \"name\": \"filesystem\",\n  \"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"range\\\": \\\"1895-1946\\\",\\n  \\\"lines\\\": {\\n    \\\"1895\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1896\\\": \\\"    def show_all_columns(self) -> None:\\\",\\n    \\\"1897\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Show all columns, sizing each to its preferred width where possible.\\\",\\n    \\\"1898\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1899\\\": \\\"        Each column is sized to its preferred width. Tabs that return None from preferred_width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1900\\\": \\\"        are treated as having the zoom-scaled default preferred width. If the total of all column\\\",\\n    \\\"1901\\\": \\\"        widths is less than the available width, symmetric spacers centre the content.\\\",\\n    \\\"1902\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1903\\\": \\\"        if len(self._tab_columns) == 0:\\\",\\n    \\\"1904\\\": \\\"            return\\\",\\n    \\\"1905\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1906\\\": \\\"        min_col_width = 200\\\",\\n    \\\"1907\\\": \\\"        style_manager = self._style_manager\\\",\\n    \\\"1908\\\": \\\"        default_col_width = style_manager.scaled_tab_width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1909\\\": \\\"        available = self.width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1910\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"1911\\\": \\\"        # Compute each column's preferred width. Tabs returning None use the default.\\\",\\n    \\\"1912\\\": \\\"        col_preferred: List[int] = []\\\",\\n    \\\"1913\\\": \\\"        for column in self._tab_columns:\\\",\\n    \\\"1914\\\": \\\"            pref: int | None = None\\\",\\n    \\\"1915\\\": \\\"            for i in range(column.count()):\\\",\\n    \\\"1916\\\": \\\"                tab = cast(TabBase, column.widget(i))\\\",\\n    \\\"1917\\\": \\\"                tab_pref = tab.preferred_width()\\\",\\n    \\\"1918\\\": \\\"                if tab_pref is not None:\\\",\\n    \\\"1919\\\": \\\"                    pr