      "content": "```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"call_3d3fe8eb3d9840bfbee374b5\",\n  \"name\": \"filesystem\",\n  \"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"range\\\": \\\"1-80\\\",\\n  \\\"lines\\\": {\\n    \\\"1\\\": \\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Base class for all preview content types.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"2\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"3\\\": \\\"import logging\\\",\\n    \\\"4\\\": \\\"from typing import List, Tuple, Callable\\\",\\n    \\\"5\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"6\\\": \\\"from PySide6.QtWidgets import QFrame, QVBoxLayout, QWidget\\\",\\n    \\\"7\\\": \\\"from PySide6.QtCore import Signal, QPoint\\\",\\n    \\\"8\\\": \\\"from PySide6.QtGui import QColor\\\",\\n    \\\"9\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"10\\\": \\\"from desktop.style_manager import StyleManager\\\",\\n    \\\"11\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"12\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"13\\\": \\\"class PreviewContentWidget(QFrame):\\\",\\n    \\\"14\\\": \\\"    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"15\\\": \\\"    Base class for all types of preview content.\\\",\\n    \\\"16\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"17\\\": \\\"    This abstract base class defines the common interface and functionality\\\",\\n    \\\"18\\\": \\\"    that all preview content types must implement. Subclasses will provide\\\",\\n    \\\"19\\\": \\\"    specific implementations for different content types (markdown, images, etc.).\\\",\\n    \\\"20\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"21\\\": \\\"    Signals:\\\",\\n    \\\"22\\\": \\\"        selection_changed: Emitted when text selection changes, with a boolean indicating if there's a selection\\\",\\n    \\\"23\\\": \\\"        scroll_requested: Emitted when scrolling is requested, with the target position\\\",\\n    \\\"24\\\": \\\"        mouse_released: Emitted when the mouse button is released\\\",\\n    \\\"25\\\": \\\"        link_clicked: Emitted when a link is clicked, with the URL\\\",\\n    \\\"26\\\": \\\"        edit_clicked: Emitted when the edit button is clicked\\\",\\n    \\\"27\\\": \\\"    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"28\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"29\\\": \\\"    selection_changed = Signal(bool)\\\",\\n    \\\"30\\\": \\\"    scroll_requested = Signal(QPoint)\\\",\\n    \\\"31\\\": \\\"    mouse_released = Signal()\\\",\\n    \\\"32\\\": \\\"    link_clicked = Signal(str)\\\",\\n    \\\"33\\\": \\\"    edit_clicked = Signal()\\\",\\n    \\\"34\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"35\\\": \\\"    def __init__(self, parent: QWidget | None = None) -> None:\\\",\\n    \\\"36\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"37\\\": \\\"        Initialize the base content widget.\\\",\\n    \\\"38\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"39\\\": \\\"        Args:\\\",\\n    \\\"40\\\": \\\"            parent: Optional parent widget\\\",\\n    \\\"41\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"42\\\": \\\"        super().__init__(parent)\\\",\\n    \\\"43\\\": \\\"        self._logger = logging.getLogger(self.__class__.__name__)\\\",\\n    \\\"44\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"45\\\": \\\"        # Set frame style\\\",\\n    \\\"46\\\": \\\"        self.setFrameStyle(QFrame.Shape.Box | QFrame.Shadow.Plain)\\\",\\n    \\\"47\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"48\\\": \\\"        # Initialize style manager\\\",\\n    \\\"49\\\": \\\"        self._style_manager = StyleManager()\\\",\\n    \\\"50\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"51\\\": \\\"        # Create layout\\\",\\n    \\\"52\\\": \\\"        self._layout = QVBoxLayout(self)\\\",\\n    \\\"53\\\": \\\"        self.setLayout(self._layout)\\\",\\n    \\\"54\\\": \\\"        self._layout.setContentsMargins(0, 0, 0, 0)\\\",\\n    \\\"55\\\": \\\"        self._layout.setSpacing(0)\\\",\\n    \\\"56\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"57\\\": \\\"    def apply_style(self) -> None:\\\",\\n    \\\"58\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"59\\\": \\\"        Apply styling to this content widget.\\\",\\n    \\\"60\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"61\\\": \\\"        This method is called when the application style changes, such as\\\",\\n    \\\"62\\\": \\\"        when the zoom factor or color scheme is updated. Subclasses should\\\",\\n    \\\"63\\\": \\\"        override this to update their specific styling.\\\",\\n    \\\"64\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"65\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"66\\\": \\\"    def has_selection(self) -> bool:\\\",\\n    \\\"67\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"68\\\": \\\"        Check if any content has selected text.\\\",\\n    \\\"69\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"70\\\": \\\"        Returns:\\\",\\n    \\\"71\\\": \\\"            True if there is selected text, False otherwise\\\",\\n    \\\"72\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"73\\\": \\\"        return False\\\",\\n    \\\"74\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"75\\\": \\\"    def get_selected_text(self) -> str:\\\",\\n    \\\"76\\\": \\\"        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"77\\\": \\\"        Get any selected text in this content.\\\",\\n    \\\"78\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"79\\\": \\\"        Returns:\\\",\\n    \\\"80\\\": \\\"            Currently selected text or empty string\\\"\\n  }\\n}\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n`content` is:\n```json\n{\n  \"range\": \"1-80\",\n  \"lines\": {\n    \"1\": \"\\\"\\\"\\\"Base class for all preview content types.\\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"2\": \"\",\n    \"3\": \"import logging\",\n    \"4\": \"from typing import List, Tuple, Callable\",\n    \"5\": \"\",\n    \"6\": \"from PySide6.QtWidgets import QFrame, QVBoxLayout, QWidget\",\n    \"7\": \"from PySide6.QtCore import Signal, QPoint\",\n    \"8\": \"from PySide6.QtGui import QColor\",\n    \"9\": \"\",\n    \"10\": \"from desktop.style_manager import StyleManager\",\n    \"11\": \"\",\n    \"12\": \"\",\n    \"13\": \"class PreviewContentWidget(QFrame):\",\n    \"14\": \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"15\": \"    Base class for all types of preview content.\",\n    \"16\": \"\",\n    \"17\": \"    This abstract base class defines the common interface and functionality\",\n    \"18\": \"    that all preview content types must implement. Subclasses will provide\",\n    \"19\": \"    specific implementations for different content types (markdown, images, etc.).\",\n    \"20\": \"\",\n    \"21\": \"    Signals:\",\n    \"22\": \"        selection_changed: Emitted when text selection changes, with a boolean indicating if there's a selection\",\n    \"23\": \"        scroll_requested: Emitted when scrolling is requested, with the target position\",\n    \"24\": \"        mouse_released: Emitted when the mouse button is released\",\n    \"25\": \"        link_clicked: Emitted when a link is clicked, with the URL\",\n    \"26\": \"        edit_clicked: Emitted when the edit button is clicked\",\n    \"27\": \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"28\": \"\",\n    \"29\": \"    selection_changed = Signal(bool)\",\n    \"30\": \"    scroll_requested = Signal(QPoint)\",\n    \"31\": \"    mouse_released = Signal()\",\n    \"32\": \"    link_clicked = Signal(str)\",\n    \"33\": \"    edit_clicked = Signal()\",\n    \"34\": \"\",\n    \"35\": \"    def __init__(self, parent: QWidget | None = None) -> None:\",\n    \"36\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"37\": \"        Initialize the base content widget.\",\n    \"38\": \"\",\n    \"39\": \"        Args:\",\n    \"40\": \"            parent: Optional parent widget\",\n    \"41\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"42\": \"        super().__init__(parent)\",\n    \"43\": \"        self._logger = logging.getLogger(self.__class__.__name__)\",\n    \"44\": \"\",\n    \"45\": \"        # Set frame style\",\n    \"46\": \"        self.setFrameStyle(QFrame.Shape.Box | QFrame.Shadow.Plain)\",\n    \"47\": \"\",\n    \"48\": \"        # Initialize style manager\",\n    \"49\": \"        self._style_manager = StyleManager()\",\n    \"50\": \"\",\n    \"51\": \"        # Create layout\",\n    \"52\": \"        self._layout = QVBoxLayout(self)\",\n    \"53\": \"        self.setLayout(self._layout)\",\n    \"54\": \"        self._layout.setContentsMargins(0, 0, 0, 0)\",\n    \"55\": \"        self._layout.setSpacing(0)\",\n    \"56\": \"\",\n    \"57\": \"    def apply_style(self) -> None:\",\n    \"58\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"59\": \"        Apply styling to this content widget.\",\n    \"60\": \"\",\n    \"61\": \"        This method is called when the application style changes, such as\",\n    \"62\": \"        when the zoom factor or color scheme is updated. Subclasses should\",\n    \"63\": \"        override this to update their specific styling.\",\n    \"64\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"65\": \"\",\n    \"66\": \"    def has_selection(self) -> bool:\",\n    \"67\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"68\": \"        Check if any content has selected text.\",\n    \"69\": \"\",\n    \"70\": \"        Returns:\",\n    \"71\": \"            True if there is selected text, False otherwise\",\n    \"72\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"73\": \"        return False\",\n    \"74\": \"\",\n    \"75\": \"    def get_selected_text(self) -> str:\",\n    \"76\": \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"\",\n    \"77\": \"        Get any selected text in this content.\",\n    \"78\": \"\",\n    \"79\": \"        Returns:\",\n    \"80\": \"            Currently selected text or empty string\"\n  }\n}\n```",
